---
source: crates/core/tests/explain.rs
expression: "rendered.join(\"\\n\\n\")"
---
[simple_threshold]
avg(last_5m):avg:system.cpu.user{env:production, service:web} > 90
→ Alert if the average over the 5 minutes of avg of `system.cpu.user` (env:production, service:web) is > 90.

[anomaly_flagship]
avg(last_1d):anomalies(sum:app.service.latency{platform:macos , country:us}.as_count(), 'agile', 5, direction='below', interval=300, seasonality='daily') >= 1
→ Alert if the average over the 1 day of anomaly detection (algorithm agile, ~5σ, direction below, daily seasonality) (sum of `app.service.latency` (platform:macos, country:us)) is ≥ 1.

[outlier_nested]
avg(last_5m):outliers(median_5(sum:app.service.requests{*} by {host}.as_count()), 'DBSCAN', 3) >= 1
→ Alert if the average over the 5 minutes of outlier detection (algorithm DBSCAN, tolerance 3) (5-point median of sum of `app.service.requests` by host) is ≥ 1.

[arithmetic_ratio]
sum(last_5m):(sum:app.service.errors{*}.as_count() / sum:app.service.requests{*}.as_count()) * 100 > 5
→ Alert if the sum over the 5 minutes of ((sum of `app.service.errors` ÷ sum of `app.service.requests`) × 100) is > 5.

[change_metric]
change(avg(last_5m),last_1h):avg:system.load.1{*} > 10
→ Alert if the average over the 5 minutes of change over last 1 hour of avg of `system.load.1` is > 10.

[log_search]
logs("status:error @http.status_code:403").index("main").rollup("count").by("service").last("5m") > 100
→ Over 5m, count log events matching `status:error @http.status_code:403`, grouped by service (rollup count), alert > 100.

[service_check]
"datadog.agent.up".over("env:prod").by("host").last(3).count_by_status()
→ Evaluates the status of service check `datadog.agent.up` over its last 3 runs grouped by host.

[slo_error_budget]
error_budget("slo-123").over("7d") > 0.5
→ Alerts when the error budget for SLO `slo-123` over 7d is > 0.5.

[composite]
123 && !456 || 789
→ Alerts when this boolean condition over other monitors holds: ((#123 && !#456) || #789).
